vertica documentation 
____________________________


I . Setting up files 

	1. donwload centos
	2. download vertica community edition
	3.download managemet console

II . installing 

	1. Install centos
	2. Install vertica rpm
		1.  #rpm -Uvh vertica-9.1.0-0.x86_64.RHEL6.rpm
		2   #rpm -Uvh vertica-console-current-version.x86_64.RHEL6.rpm
			//tip shared location file system  mnt/hdfs  if not work try 
			//Linux-WinSCP
		3. yum install dialog        //if dilog  error shows
		4. install the scripts
			#/opt/vertica/sbin/install_vertica --host 127.0.0.1  --rpm /root/vertica-9.1.0-0.x86_64.RHEL6.rpm --dba-user ram --failure-threshold NONE


III. to  start server
	
	1. #su dbadmin   //default user for  vertica
	2. # cd
	3. #admintools
		no.6  configuration menu
		no.1 create database
			//tip error log stored in opt/vertica/log/admintools



IV. to  unintall 

	1. rpm -e pacakgename      (tip  without .x86_64.rpm)




